                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230115-57-victim617 t18230115-57-viclabel330"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18230115-57-crimeloc331">King's-road, Chelsea</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230115-57-crimeloc331" type="placeName" value="King's-road, Chelsea"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230115-57-crimeloc331" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230115-57-off328 t18230115-57-crimeloc331"></join>. On Saturday morning, the 21st of December, about eight o'clock, I left my shop with the glass case about six inches outside the window; the glass<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182301150031"></xptr>was perfect. I returned about half-past three, and found it broken, and missed two seals and a necklace, worth 50 s.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230115-57-person619">
                  JAMES 
                  WISE
               <interp inst="t18230115-57-person619" type="surname" value="WISE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230115-57-person619" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230115-57-person619" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live opposite to Mr. Styles. On Saturday morning, about ten o'clock I saw the prisoner pass the door - he went up to the glass case, I saw him break the the glass, and then with a wire take out this property. I crossed over, and seized him in the act of taking the last seal, and saw them drop from him into the area.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was passing, and stopped to look at the window, two men stood there. I saw the glass was broken, looked at the one who stood by me, and he went away; this gentleman came and took me.</p>
